        "statement_id": "doc::panic.md::section:0001::statement:001",
        "statement_text": "r[panic.intro] Rust provides a mechanism to prevent a function from returning normally, and instead \"panic,\" which is a response to an error condition that is typically not expected to be recoverable within the context in which the error is encountered. r[panic.lang-ops] Some language constructs, such as out-of-bounds [array indexing], panic automatically. r[panic.control] There are also language features that provide a level of control over panic behavior: * A [_panic handler_][panic handler] defines the behavior of a panic. * [FFI ABIs](items/functions.md#unwinding) may alter how panics behave. > [!NOTE] > The standard library provides the capability to explicitly panic via the [`panic!` macro][panic!]. r[panic.panic_handler]",
        "text_sha256": "4ada57ff3ab72fa6e8dc5e8cdd7ab16f7cba90a036130641de4c240b2604d015",
        "token_overlap_count": 0
      },
